rComments: What can I say that hasn't already been said about Prof Murray?  She's incredibly kind and wants students to succeed, and her lectures are always fascinating (slightly concept-heavy but in a good way).  She leaves tons of feedback and is very approachable.  Take her classes if you get the chance, period!

One of the best professor in my opinion. Very knowledgable in her field and passionate about her work. 4 out of 8 workshops are mandatory. However, she does not post anything in the "grade" section of Brightspace. Thus, unless you inquire your participation grade (which is a big chunk of your overall), you will not know.
Most understanding, caring, prof. Very easy course with very engaging content. Most flexible prof I've ever had.

Professor Murray is simply the best!  The most caring professor I've ever had at uOttawa.  She is very accommodating and her passion for the subject is clear.  I recommend taking any class that she teaches.

I've had the pleasure to have her twice thus far, and she never fails to be a wonderful professor. Even if you aren't very interested in the subject her passion makes up for it and makes for both engaging lectures and discussions. She's highly accessible outside of class, very helpful and understanding/respectful of her students. She's the best!

Professor Murray is one of the best professors that I've ever had during my studies. She is considerate and allows for very deep and interesting discussions in class. Since it was a seminar course, we did have quite a bit of readings, but nothing more than usual. I would highly recommend any of her classes.

Professor Murray is one of the best professors you'll ever have. I've taken 3 classes with her and could not recommend her enough. Her lectures are interesting and discussion classes are captivating. I highly, highly recommend taking a class with her if you can!
Heather Murray is the best prof you will ever have.

Absolutely love prof. Murray. Such a kind and caring person and super understanding. When I took her course I was going through a rough time, and she was incredibly accommodating and I could tell she really wanted me to succeed and pass her course. Her lectures were interesting and very clear. Professors like her are needed way more at uOttawa.

Lectures are interesting and a really good length, no complaints here. Professor Murray was easy to contact and gave good feedback without exception. You can really see that she's passionate about the subject and cares about her students. Would definitely recommend to anybody thinking of taking one of her courses.

Professor Murray is a wonderful lecturer and unbelievably kind and compassionate. For a Tues/Fri split, Tuesday lectures were pre-recorded and posted in smaller chunks and Friday zoom discussion groups with graded participation. The recorded lectures were always interesting and the zoom discussion was great too, despite the circumstances.

I love this professor so much. She made me become more interested in history and I even read, during the summer, a history related book she recommended, and it was amazing. She's so sweet, and just such a great prof and person.

She was the sweetest! Super nice and a good lecturer, participation is graded though. The material was very interesting but there was a lot of work which was very tiring. I took it as an elective and it was my lowest grade this year. The grading criteria is also pretty unclear, I didn't really know how they were grading certain things
Very funny! Very friendly! You can tell she is really interested in the subject. Sometimes a student would ask a question and she would only answer part of it, but other than that 10/10
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Amazing, probably one of the best proffs i've ever had

She was okay enough. Her lectures were fine, and her assignments were fun to do. I will take her classes again if possible. I have no complaints and got to learn a lot of new things. Beware if you don't like talking in class, as a large chunk of your grade comes from participation in class, meaning talking in front of everyone.

The best professor I've had in university. She's super accessible, a great lecturer and encourages class participation in a way few profs I've had do. Dealt with the pandemic with a lot of flexibility and compassion. Learnt a lot. Take her course if you get the chance - you won't regret it.

I was worried to take a third year class, but Prof. Murray showed me that I had nothing to be worried about. She is incredibly engaging in her lectures, provides extra reading (which is not compulsory, just something she thinks is interesting), and gives encouraging feedback. And if you're lucky, she may bring in historical baking from time to time

I've taken two classes with Murray, a 3000 level history course and a 4000 level seminar and she is literally the best. My favourite prof I've had hands down. Wants you to succeed, always available to help and provides tons of commentary! Super understanding and knowledgeable. Has lots of reading recommendations. Take a class with her if you can!
Professor Murray is a pleasure to deal with. Extremely knowledgeable and genuinely cares about her students.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Professor Murray is one of the best profs Ive ever had. Shes so passionate and knowledgeable, and she privileged class discussions of primary source readings. She gives pages of helpful feedback even for small assignments. She is so welcoming and caring to her students. A bit of a tough grader but she really tries to help her students improve.

She is an amazing teacher and clearly very passionate about her subject (American History). You will not regret taking her course. It is quite a bit of work but she brings the material to life and keeps students engaged. She is always approachable and helpful.
Prof. Murray is one of the best professors I've had. Her enthusiasm for learning is infectious.  She is genuinely invested in her students, and will help you succeed.

Great prof who sets up very useful mandatory assignments that end up being the basis of your paper and final. Total of 4 assignments including the take home final. For people who are better at papers, she's the ideal prof. Course pack was used for final. Participation does matter, but is not mandatory to pass (went to 3 lectures, got a B+).

Hands down one of the top 5 greatest prof's at uOttawa. She's the kindest professor I've had so far and she goes out of her way to provide you the greatest feedback on your essay. For this class all you need to work on is your essay writing skills. She also bakes for the class and does her best to remember your name in a class of 100+.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Honestly one of the best professors I've ever had. Murray genuinely cares about the stuff she is teaching. She uses a lot of primary sources and always has recommended books for each topic covered in class in case you are particularly enthralled. A+ teacher and great person. Textbook was online and free which was awesome too!

This class was amazing. I didn't think I would like it but I LOVED it. The cultural aspect was very interesting and Prof Murray was simply outstanding. Only thing is, she is a very difficult marker. Three written assignments and final take home exam. Make an effort to speak with her during office hours. She's also very accommodating with assignment

Heather is the cutest, sweetest, most caring prof I've ever had. She is very approachable and never talks down to students: she will giggle along with you and makes you feel like you're saying something really valuable when you talk to her. Her lectures are interesting, she always shows videos, and even bakes sometimes. Her fav word is fascinating!

HANDS DOWN the best history professor at the University of Ottawa. She has insanely interesting lectures and her discussions are the best of any history class I've been in. She makes a point of memorizing students' names, which is also awesome. The classes kinda end up feeling like a big family!

Professor Murray prepared an excellent course - there isn't a lot more to say about it! You are doing yourself a favour by taking her class. She is a wonderful human being, and if you demonstrate your interest in the slightest, she makes a great academic reference should you intend to pursue a further degree.

Such a great class and Heather herself is phenomenal. You know she loves her stuff, lectures are always engaging. 3 papers, 1 take home final, and fair marker with /plenty/ of helpful comments. While office hours are great for help, she's just fantastic to talk with as well. Also bakes on occasion for class. Can't do her enough justice: take her.

Heather is amazing. She's inspirational, you learn so much and it's fairly easy. 3 papers, 1 take home final. As well, she's a pretty easy marker. I hated the few times I missed her class because I learned so much and they were so much fun. If you have the chance, taker her class, you won't regret it.

Great prof & person! Takes time to put thoughtful comments in your papers that really helped me improve on future ones. She also marks a lot herself. No in class exams. She's super passionate about her subjects. Go to her classes! She provides tons of verbal information within her lecture, which makes her classes stimulating and you learn a lot!
Interesting class and Heather is very enthusiastic about what she teaches and is helpful and nice. There are a few assignment but they are pretty straight forward and interesting.

Prof. Murray knows her stuff and the way she structures her course is very engaging. Get ready to read lots and participate in class as she makes a point to learn her students' names (a very nice gesture I think, as one can get lost in the sea of students at UofO).pay attention, do the readings, participate, ask questions + you'll get a good grade
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: What a great prof! Shes so nice and helpful. A real saint. Loves her material, gets very excited about it. Shes very clear and concise. I believe theres just a coursepack. Had a lot of fun in her class.

Prof. Murray had taken a subject that is not so easily conveyable into a course that brought a wide variety of teaching methods into something that was extremely enjoyable. Take her course, you won't regret it. She is a fantastic prof.

Really fantastic. Makes you feel welcome. Engages you. Learns your name. Bakes. So sweet and a really interesting and easy to listen to lecturer. Great prof. Would take more class with her if I had the time to do all the required readings... They are a bit too extensive.
She is very committed, but demands a high amount of reading.

Heather is the best professor I have ever had. She truly cares for her students and takes the time to get know them (she sent me a clip from NPR out of the blue because she thought I'd find it interesting). Changed how I view American history.
She was great
Have had her three times now. A woman of my dreams. Sweet, cute, geeky, and a baker. It makes me happy to be in her class!
She made the material really interesting and with a variety of approaches. Also the assignments were unique and interesting. I really liked this class.
How could anyone dislike her ? She's lovely. Great teacher, one of the best I had so far.

As always, she proved to be perhaps the best Professor in the department.  Very interesting lectures and assignments.  Readings weren't too heavy and evaluations reflected the material covered.  She's also an insanely nice lady and very funny!  Recommended without hesitation.
Best professor I have had so far. Would recommend to everyone who is interested in American history.
She is lovely! In ALL senses of the word. She's also whip smart, but not in an intimidating way. I can't say I like her "historical baking" but it's very funny that she tries to bake from the era!!

Such a sweetheart. She is so dedicated to her work and her passion of history, you can't help but also get excited in what she is teaching. Definitely drop by her office or give her an email; she is always so enthusiastic and willing to help with any issue, or just talk about books. You'll definitely leave her class smiling.

Heather Murray was such an awesome prof.  Very passionate about what she teaches, and certainly knows her stuff.  She seems like a real sweetheart, and will still say hi to you after you're done with her class.  And she brought cookies!!  How many profs do THAT? :D
The best Professor I have ever had, cares about her students and loves her job.
It makes me happy to be around her. Watch for the struggle with the V-8 straw at the beginning of every class--she's so very adorkable!!

Absolutely incredible. Super enthusiastic and fun, REALLY great lectures. She realizes that not everyone reads the text book, so she provides tons of ways to get more from the material. One of the best profs I've had, she's incredibly interesting and very very helpful. Gets to know her students, I can't say enough good things in 350 characters.

Best professor I have yet to have. She is so passionate about what she teaches that it makes you want to come to class and hear what she has to say. Extremely helpful, encourages you to come see her about papers, tests etc. Responds to emails within hours sometimes even minutes and is very funny! Highly reccommend any class taught by her!

Prof Murray is absolutely fantastic. Very informative in class and a reasonable marker. Emailed her a year after taking her course for reading recommendations and she responded within 24 hours. A phenomenal prof; actually interested in educations - all profs should be like her.

Professor Murray was incredible! I didn't really know what to expect with it being my first American History course. She was awesome, loved every class! I studied so much for the exam because I loved the course so much! I have her again this year and can't wait!

My grandmother is cooler than she is, but I still find her cute anyhow! (Heather Murray, not my grandmother). And Grandma loves V-8 too! Definitely try a class with her even if you don't like U.S. history because it's more about ideas.
One of the best Profs I have ever had. She is passionate, helpful, and absolutely hilarious. Take every and any class you can get into!

She was a great prof. She made US history intriguing and accessible. Watched video or radio clips at the end of every class. I didn't expect anything at the start of term but was pleasantly suprised both by marks and enjoyment. Attend class and do ALL the readings to get good grades. Also is a relatively easy marker.
My favorite Professor by far...
DORKALICIOUS!!!

Dr. Murray is an awesome prof.  This was my favourite class all year because of her!  Her enthusiasm and interest in what she lectures about is amazing, as well as her depth of knowledge.  The videos she shows during class are great for contextualization also.  She also brings in "traditional 1950s American baking."  Take this class with her!

I LOVE her. She has interesting things to say and her teaching methods are unconventional (she actually likes to listen to what students have to say!). I would recommend her to anyone if you would like a new and refreshing take on American history. Also, the constant V-8 is adorable.

I took her class last year and I really enjoyed it. She gives interesting lectures and she seems like a really kind person. As for having a crush on her, I get that but unfortunately I think her heart belongs to books. If you told her that she would probably say 'Oh? Huh. Well, you know, there's a very interesting book on the history of crushes!'

I have a major crush on her and I'm really obvious about it but she doesn't seem to notice at all! She just stands there swaying back and forth, sipping her V-8 and whatever's in the Germany bottle. She's amazing.

Absolutely loved this class! I hate US history with a passion, but I've registered for another class with her next year because she makes the material interesting and relevant. Bit of a hard marker, but she's fair, and explains why you got the marks she gives. Actually ENJOYED reading the text book and going to lectures!!

Her enthusiasm is infectious. Excellent course breakdown and class is always fun to attend (thats right FUN). Always assigns an essay but gives precise criteria and assistance to do well. Her comments about your work are specific. TAKE HER CLASS, you will not regret it!
I'm in love with her as well. She's a Big Dork! (believes in ufos, drinks V-8 constantly) but that makes her really approachable. I will take whatever class she teaches.
Extremely able as an educator, and very helpful outside of class hours. Incredibly understanding, be sure to grab a class with her if you can!
I'm totally in love with Heather Murray!! She's just so cute. Definitely take a class with her!
I love her class and she's very cute as well! I saw her downtown drinking a V-8...lol

Heather Murray is absolutely fantastic.  She transmits with ease her extensive knowledge of the subject as well as he infectious passion.  Her use of visual and audio sources is both interesting and helpful.  I would strongly recommend you to follow some of her classes.  :)

What can I say...she made a boring class-like American Revolution- actually interesting!! Her enthusiasm and love for the subject brought energy to the class. Classes are based on the text, so do the reading and everything becomes crystal. Love this prof..would def. take another one of her classes!!
